Apolo Ohno.label: Apolo Ohno
Apolo Ohno.description:
Apolo Anton Ohno is a retired American short track speed skating competitor and an eight-time medalist in the Winter Olympics.
Raised by his father, Ohno began training full-time in 1996. Wikipedia
Apolo Ohno.Born: May 22, 1982 (age 31), Federal Way, Washington, United States
Education: University of Colorado at Colorado Springs

Gerard Kemkers.label: Gerard Kemkers
Gerard Kemkers.description: Gerard Kemkers is a former speed skater from the Netherlands, who represented his native country at the 1988 Winter Olympics in Calgary, Canada. There he won the bronze medal in the 5000 metres. Wikipedia

Shannon Rempel.label: Shannon Rempel
Shannon Rempel.description: Shannon Rempel is a Canadian speed skater. An Olympic silver medalist from the 2006 Winter Olympics in the team pursuit. World Champion in the team pursuit from 2007 World Single Distance Championships, SLC, UT. Wikipedia

Tuomas Nieminen.label: Tuomas Nieminen
Tuomas Nieminen.description: Tuomas Nieminen is a Finnish long track speed skater who participates in international competitions. Wikipedia

Wouter Olde Heuvel.label: Wouter Olde Heuvel
Wouter Olde Heuvel.description: Wouter Olde Heuvel is a Dutch long track speed skater who participates in international competitions. Wikipedia

Choi Eun-Kyung.label: Choi Eun-Kyung
Choi Eun-Kyung.description: Choi Eun-Kyung is a South Korean short track speed skater. She is a double Olympic Champion in relays and a two-time Overall World Champion for 2003 and 2004. Wikipedia

Erik Hulzebosch.label: Erik Hulzebosch
Erik Hulzebosch.description:
Erik Hulzebosch is a Dutch marathon speed skater, inline speed skater and part-time singer and blogger at his own website.
Born in Ane, Gramsbergen Hulzebosch started as a cyclo-cross cyclist. Wikipedia

Kim Yun-Mi (speed skater).label: Kim Yun-mi
Kim Yun-Mi (speed skater).description:
Kim Yunmi is a South Korean short track speed skater, who won gold medals in the 3000 m relay at the 1994 and 1998 Winter Olympics.
Kim won her first Olympic gold medal at the 1994 Winter Olympics in Lillehammer at only thirteen years of age. Wikipedia

Jeff Simon.label: Jeff Simon
Jeff Simon.description:
Jeffrey Simon is an American short track speed skater and three-time bronze medallist at the World Championships.
At the 2011 World Short Track Speed Skating Championships in Sheffield, England, Simon won three bronze medals. Wikipedia

Yvonne van Gennip.label: Yvonne van Gennip
Yvonne van Gennip.description: Yvonne Maria van Gennip is one of the most successful female Dutch all-round speed skaters. Her main success dates from the 1988 Winter Olympics in Calgary, where she unexpectedly won three gold medals. Wikipedia

Arjen van der Kieft.label: Arjen van der Kieft
Arjen van der Kieft.description: Arjen van der Kieft is a Dutch long-distance speed skater. He competed for the Netherlands at the 2010 Winter Olympics in the Men's 10000 m, where he finished 9th. Wikipedia

Heather Richardson.label: Heather Richardson
Heather Richardson.description: Heather Richardson is an American speed skater who has competed since 2006. She represented the United States at the 2010 Winter Olympics in Vancouver, where she finished 6th in 500 metres, 9th in the 1000 metres, and 16th in the 1500 metres. Wikipedia
Heather Richardson.Born: March 20, 1989 (age 25), High Point, North Carolina, United States

Koen Verweij.label: Koen Verweij
Koen Verweij.description: Koen Verweij is a Dutch speedskater and inline speed skater. At the end of the skating season 2008–09 he made a transfer from the Jong Oranje team of the national skating union to the commercial team of TVM. Wikipedia

Travis Jayner.label: Travis Jayner
Travis Jayner.description: Travis Jayner is a Canadian-born American short track speed skater who is a member of the US Olympic Team for the 2010 Winter Olympics in Vancouver. Wikipedia

Valérie Maltais.label: Valérie Maltais
Valérie Maltais.description: Valérie Maltais is a Canadian short-track speed skater. She has won six world championship medals including finishing second overall in 2012. Wikipedia

Ryan Bedford.label: Ryan Bedford
Ryan Bedford.description: Ryan Bedford is an American speed skater who competed at the 2010 Winter Olympics. Wikipedia

Bob de Vries.label: Bob de Vries
Bob de Vries.description: Bob de Vries is a Dutch professional marathon speed skater and long track speed skater. He is the brother of Elma de Vries. Wikipedia

Atje Keulen-Deelstra.label: Atje Keulen-Deelstra
Atje Keulen-Deelstra.description: Atje Keulen-Deelstra was a Dutch speed skater, who was a four-fold World Allround Champion between the age of 32 and 36. Wikipedia

Hilbert van der Duim.label: Hilbert van der Duim
Hilbert van der Duim.description: Hilbert van der Duim is a former speed skater. A two-time world and European champion, Van der Duim "won often but also fell often", and has become famous for some of the incidents that happened to him during his career. Wikipedia

Ids Postma.label: Ids Postma
Ids Postma.description: Ids Hylke Postma is a Dutch former speed skater. He is an Olympic gold medalist and former world champion. Wikipedia

Elma de Vries.label: Elma de Vries
Elma de Vries.description: Elma de Vries is a Dutch marathon speed skater and inline speed skater. She is the older sister of marathon speed skater Bob de Vries. Wikipedia

Jamie Gregg.label: Jamie Gregg
Jamie Gregg.description:
Jamie Gregg is a Canadian long track speed skater.
Gregg was ranked 10th in overall World Cup standings for the 2009–10 season. He is set to compete for Canada at the 2010 Winter Olympics in the 500 m. Wikipedia

Jessica Gregg.label: Jessica Gregg
Jessica Gregg.description:
Jessica Gregg is a Canadian short track speed skater.
Jessica Gregg was the only member of the 2010 Canadian Olympic short track team outside of Quebec. Wikipedia

Jan Ykema.label: Jan Ykema
Jan Ykema.description: Jan Jelte Ykema is a former ice speed skater from the Netherlands, who represented his native country at two consecutive Winter Olympics, starting in 1984 in Sarajevo, Yugoslavia. In 1988 he won the silver medal in the men's 500 metres. Wikipedia

Lieuwe de Boer.label: Lieuwe de Boer
Lieuwe de Boer.description: Lieuwe de Boer is a former ice speed skater from the Netherlands, who represented his native country at the 1980 Winter Olympics in Lake Placid, United States. There he won the bronze medal in the men's 500 metres. Wikipedia

Maria Sterk.label: Maria Sterk
Maria Sterk.description:
Maria Sterk is a Dutch marathon speed skater.
In 2005 she finished in third position of the Essent Cup and on 11 February of that year she announced to attack the women's world hour speed skating record, which was held by Lian van Tol at that time. Wikipedia

Marrit Leenstra (speed skater).label: Marrit Leenstra
Marrit Leenstra (speed skater).description: Marrit Leenstra is a Dutch long track speed skater. Wikipedia

Pim Mulier.label: Pim Mulier
Pim Mulier.description: Willem Johan Herman Mulier, known as Pim Mulier was one of the leading figures in sporting history of the Netherlands. Wikipedia

Renske Vellinga.label: Renske Vellinga
Renske Vellinga.description: Renske Vellinga was an ice speed skater from the Netherlands, who won a bronze and a silver medal at the 1993 Dutch distance championships. Wikipedia

Rintje Ritsma.label: Rintje Ritsma
Rintje Ritsma.description: Robert Rintje Ritsma is a former Dutch long track speed skater. His nickname is the Beer van Lemmer, which translates to the Bear from Lemmer, analogous to Igor Zhelezovski's nickname "The Bear from ... Wikipedia

Tonny de Jong.label: Tonny de Jong
Tonny de Jong.description: Tonny de Jong is a former Dutch speed skater, who was raised in Heerenveen and now lives in Calgary with Canadian speed skater Mark Knoll, whom she married in 2003. Wikipedia

Yep Kramer.label: Yep Kramer
Yep Kramer.description: Yep Kramer is a Dutch-Frisian long track and marathon speed skater. He is the father of speed skaters Sven Kramer and Brecht Kramer. Wikipedia

Roger Schneider.label: Roger Schneider
Roger Schneider.description: Roger Schneider is a Swiss long track speed skater who participates in international competitions. Wikipedia

Ans Schut.label: Ans Schut
Ans Schut.description:
Johanna Schut is a former ice speed skater from the Netherlands.
Ans Schut had her best year in 1968 when, after winning silver at the World Allround Championships, she became Olympic Champion on the 3,000 m at the 1968 Winter Olympics in Grenoble. Wikipedia

Haralds Silovs.label: Haralds Silovs
Haralds Silovs.description: Haralds Silovs is a Latvian long track and former short track speed skater, who became the 2008 European champion in short track. Wikipedia

Heike Warnicke.label: Heike Warnicke
Heike Warnicke.description:
Heike Warnicke is a German speed skater who competed in the 1992 Winter Olympics and in the 1994 Winter Olympics.
She was born in Weimar. Wikipedia

Antoine Gélinas-Beaulieu.label: Antoine Gélinas-Beaulieu
Antoine Gélinas-Beaulieu.description: Antoine Gélinas-Beaulieu is a Canadian short track speed skater from Sherbrooke, Quebec currently residing in Montreal. He is currently a member of the national junior short track team for Canada. Wikipedia

Barbara de Loor.label: Barbara de Loor
Barbara de Loor.description: Barbara de Loor is a retired Dutch speed skater who was specialised in the middle long and longer distances, over 1000 to 5000 metres. Wikipedia

Carry Geijssen.label: Carry Geijssen
Carry Geijssen.description:
Carolina Cornelia Catharina Geijssen is a former speed skater from the Netherlands.
Carry Geijssen won silver at the Dutch Allround Championships in 1965. In 1966, she became Dutch Allround Champion. Wikipedia

Alyson Dudek.label: Alyson Dudek
Alyson Dudek.description: Alyson Dudek is an American short track speed skater and Olympic bronze medallist. Wikipedia
Alyson Dudek.Born: July 30, 1990 (age 23), Hales Corners, Wisconsin, United States

Anastasia Bucsis.label: Anastasia Bucsis
Anastasia Bucsis.description:
Anastasia Bucsis is a Canadian speed skater. She competed at the 2010 Winter Olympics in Vancouver in the women's 500-metre competition.
She will compete in the Sochi 2014 Winter Olympics for women's long track. Wikipedia

Blake Skjellerup.label: Blake Skjellerup
Blake Skjellerup.description: Blake Skjellerup is a short track speed skater who competed for New Zealand at the 2010 Winter Olympics; finishing sixteenth. Wikipedia

Caroline Calvé.label: Caroline Calve
Caroline Calvé.description:
Caroline Calvé is a Canadian snowboarder.
She competed at the 2010 Winter Olympics in Vancouver in the women's parallel giant slalom competition. Wikipedia

Jelmer Beulenkamp.label: Jelmer Beulenkamp
Jelmer Beulenkamp.description:
Jelmer Beulenkamp is a former speed skater. He was the Dutch speed skating champion in 1998. In 2003, he switched to marathon skating.
In his speed skating career Beulenkamp skated one world record. Wikipedia

Jonathan Kuck.label: Jonathan Kuck
Jonathan Kuck.description:
Jonathan Kuck is an American speed skater and silver medalist in the Winter Olympics.
At the 2010 Winter Olympics, Kuck won a silver medal in the team pursuit along with Brian Hansen and Chad Hedrick. Wikipedia

Jordan Malone.label: Jordan Malone
Jordan Malone.description: Jordan Malone is an American short track speed skater who was a member of the US Olympic Team for the 2010 Winter Olympics in Vancouver. He is from Denton, Texas, and is an alumnus of the Texas Tech University Independent School District. Wikipedia

Julie Wendel Lundholdt.label: Julie-Wendel Lundholdt
Julie Wendel Lundholdt.description: Julie Wendel Lundholdt is a Danish snowboarder from Copenhagen, Denmark. Julie Lundholdt is currently not ranked and has paused her professional snowboard carrier. Wikipedia

Kwak Yoon-Gy.label: Kwak Yoon-Gy
Kwak Yoon-Gy.description: Kwak Yoon-Gy is a South Korean short track speed skater. He is the 2012 Overall World Champion. Wikipedia

Kyle Parrott.label: Kyle Parrott
Kyle Parrott.description:
Kyle Parrott is a Canadian long track speed skater.
He competed at the 2010 Winter Olympics in Vancouver in the men's 500 metre, 1000 metre and 1500 metre competitions. Wikipedia

Lana Gehring.label: Lana Gehring
Lana Gehring.description: Lana Gehring is an American short track speed skater. Wikipedia

Palmer Taylor.label: Palmer Taylor
Palmer Taylor.description:
Palmer Taylor is a Canadian snowboarder.
She competed at the 2010 Winter Olympics in Vancouver in the women's halfpipe competition. Wikipedia

Simon Cho.label: Simon Cho
Simon Cho.description: Simon Cho is an American short track speed skater who was a member of the US Olympic Team for the 2010 Winter Olympics in Vancouver. Wikipedia

Tamara Oudenaarden.label: Tamara Oudenaarden
Tamara Oudenaarden.description:
Tamara Oudenaarden is a Canadian long track speed skater.
She was an alternate skater at the 2010 Winter Olympics in Vancouver in the women's 500 metre competition, but did not race in the event since all other qualifying Canadian skaters competed. Wikipedia

Tatiana Borodulina.label: Tatiana Borodulina
Tatiana Borodulina.description: Tatiana Aleksandrovna Borodulina is a Russian short-track speed skater, who formerly represented Australia. Wikipedia

Eric Kraan.label: Eric Kraan
Eric Kraan.description: Eric Rijk Kraan Osmanchuk is a Mexican business owner and former Mexican National Team speedskater. He resides in the US and is co-owner and co-CEO of the SkateNow Shop, a US-based speedskating equipment retailer. Wikipedia

Kim Tae-Hoon.label: Kim Tae-hoon
Kim Tae-Hoon.description:
Kim Tae-Hoon is a South Korean short track speed skater.
At the 2011 Winter Universiade, Kim won the gold medal in the men's 1000 metre events. He added silver in the 1500 metres. Wikipedia

Kjeld Nuis.label: Kjeld Nuis
Kjeld Nuis.description: Kjeld Nuis is a Dutch speed skater. Wikipedia

Michael Gilday.label: Michael Gilday
Michael Gilday.description:
Michael Gilday is a Canadian short track speed skater from Yellowknife, Northwest Territories.
Gilday is a member of the Canadian Olympic Team Competing in the 1500m and 5000m relay Short Track Speed Skating at the Sochi Olympics. Wikipedia

Pat McNamara (speed skater).label: Pat McNamara
Pat McNamara (speed skater).description: Pat McNamara was an American speed skater. He competed at the 1952 and 1956 Winter Olympics. Wikipedia

Olivier Jean.label: Olivier Jean
Olivier Jean.description: Olivier Jean is a Canadian short track speed skater from Lachenaie, Quebec currently residing in Montreal. He is a well-known figure for his dreadlocks and for listening to reggae, which he says makes him skate faster. Wikipedia

Wang Meng (speed skater).label: Wang Meng
Wang Meng (speed skater).description: Wang Meng is a Chinese short track speed skater. She is a four-time Olympic Champion and 2008 and 2009 Overall World Champion. She is the most decorated Chinese Winter Olympic athlete ever with four Olympic gold medals, a silver and a bronze. Wikipedia

Marianne St-Gelais.label: Marianne St-Gelais
Marianne St-Gelais.description: Marianne St-Gelais is a Canadian short track speed skater. She won two silver medals in the 500 m and 3,000 m events at the Vancouver 2010 Winter Olympics. Wikipedia

Cho Ha-Ri.label: Cho Ha-ri
Cho Ha-Ri.description: Cho Ha-Ri is a short track speed skater who competes for South Korea. She is the 2011 Overall World Champion. Wikipedia

François Hamelin.label: Francois Hamelin
François Hamelin.description: François Hamelin is a Canadian short track speed skater from Sainte-Julie, Quebec, currently residing in Montreal. He is the younger brother of acclaimed Canadian short tracker Charles Hamelin. Wikipedia

Hege Bøkko.label: Hege Bøkko
Hege Bøkko.description: Hege Bøkko is a Norwegian long-track speedskater, and the younger sister of Håvard Bøkko. Wikipedia

Mo Tae-Bum.label: Mo Tae-Bum
Mo Tae-Bum.description: Mo Tae-bum is a South Korean speed skater. He is the 2010 Olympic Champion and the 2012 and 2013 World Champion in 500 m. He started speedskating while in the third grade. Wikipedia

Noh Jin-Kyu.label: Noh Jin-kyu
Noh Jin-Kyu.description: Noh Jin-Kyu is a South Korean short track speed skater. During his first season at the senior level at the age of 18, he became the 2011 Overall World Champion. He is the World Record holder for 1500m and 3000m. Wikipedia

Sung Si-Bak.label: Sung Si-Bak
Sung Si-Bak.description: Sung Si-Bak is a South Korean short track speed skater. At the 2007 Winter Universiade, he won all five short track speed skating events. Wikipedia

Sven Kramer.label: Sven Kramer
Sven Kramer.description: Sven Kramer is a Dutch long track speed skater. He is the Olympic champion of the 5000 meter in Vancouver 2010, as well in Sochi 2014, six-time European, and six-time World Allround Champion. Wikipedia

Brian Hansen (speed skater).label: Brian Hansen
Brian Hansen (speed skater).description:
Brian Hansen is an American speed skater and silver medalist in the Winter Olympics.
At the 2010 Winter Olympics, Hansen won a silver medal in the team pursuit along with Jonathan Kuck and Chad Hedrick. Wikipedia

Katherine Reutter.label: Katherine Reutter
Katherine Reutter.description: Katherine Reutter is a former American short track speed skater. She is a two-time medalist in the Winter Olympics, 2011 overall world silver medalist and the 2010–2011 overall ISU Short Track Speed Skating World Cup champion. Wikipedia

Leah Poulos.label: Leah Poulos
Leah Poulos.description:
Leah Jean Poulos is a former speed skater.
Leah Poulos specialized in the sprint events and made her international debut at the World Sprint Championships in 1970, where she won a silver medal in the 500 meter event. Wikipedia

Nancy Swider-Peltz, Jr.label: Nancy Swider-Peltz Jr.
Nancy Swider-Peltz, Jr.description: Nancy Swider-Peltz, Jr. is an American speed skater who competed at the 2010 Winter Olympics. Wikipedia

Paulien van Deutekom.label: Paulien van Deutekom
Paulien van Deutekom.description: Paulien van Deutekom is a former Dutch speed skater who specialised in the middle long distances, over 1000 and 1500 metres. Wikipedia

Shani Davis.label: Shani Davis
Shani Davis.description:
Shani Davis is an Olympic Champion speed skater from the United States.
At the 2006 Winter Olympics in Turin, Italy, Davis became the first black athlete to win a gold medal in an individual sport at ... Wikipedia

Trevor Marsicano.label: Trevor Marsicano
Trevor Marsicano.description:
Trevor Marsicano is an American long-track speedskater and silver medalist in the Winter Olympics.
At the 2010 Winter Olympics, Marsicano won a silver medal for his part in the team pursuit. Wikipedia
Trevor Marsicano.Born: April 5, 1989 (age 24), Schenectady, New York, United States

Jan Bols.label: Jan Bols
Jan Bols.description:
Jan Bols is a former Dutch long track speed skater.
Bols was among the top all-rounders in the late 60s and early 70s, this period overlapped the glory days of Kees Verkerk and Ard Schenk, so that he ... Wikipedia

Karolína Erbanová.label: Karolína Erbanová
Karolína Erbanová.description: Karolína Erbanová is a Czech long track speed skater. Wikipedia

Thijsje Oenema.label: Thijsje Oenema
Thijsje Oenema.description:
Thijsje Oenema is a Dutch speedskater and "short-track sprinter". She is specialised on the short distances.
Oenema skates for the VPZ-skating team and is a member for skating club S.T.D. Sint Nicolaasga. Wikipedia

Dolph van der Scheer.label: Dolph van der Scheer
Dolph van der Scheer.description:
Adolph "Dolph" Frederik van der Scheer was a Dutch speed skater who competed in the 1936 Winter Olympics.
He was born in Zutphen. Wikipedia

Mariska Huisman.label: Mariska Huisman
Mariska Huisman.description: Mariska Huisman is a Dutch marathon skater and speed skater. She was the first winner of a mass start worldcup in Astana. At this moment she is the number 2 on the world ranking list. Wikipedia

Leo Visser.label: Leo Visser
Leo Visser.description: Leendert "Leo" Visser is s a former Dutch Speed skater, who in 1989 won the World Allround championship, the same year in which Visser also became European champion. Wikipedia

Coen de Koning.label: Coen de Koning
Coen de Koning.description: Coen de Koning was twice winner of the Elfstedentocht and the second Dutch speed skating World Champion. Wikipedia

Ivar Ballangrud.label: Ivar Ballangrud
Ivar Ballangrud.description: Ivar Eugen Ballangrud was a Norwegian speed skater, a four-time Olympic champion in speed skating. As the only triple gold medalist at the 1936 Winter Olympics, Ballangrud was the most successful athlete there. Wikipedia

Joe Donoghue.label: Joe Donoghue
Joe Donoghue.description: Joseph F. Donoghue was a speed skater. He became the speed skating World Champion in 1891. He was a member of the Manhattan Athletic Club. Wikipedia
Joe Donoghue.Born: February 11, 1871, Newburgh, New York, United States

Harm Kuipers.label: Harm Kuipers
Harm Kuipers.description:
Harm Kuipers is a former speed skater from the Netherlands.
Kuipers combined his sports careers with being a Medicine student at the University of Groningen. Wikipedia

Annette Gerritsen.label: Annette Gerritsen
Annette Gerritsen.description: Annette Albertine Gerritsen is a Dutch speed skater. She specialises in the 500 m and 1000 m distances, and won a silver medal in the 1000 metres at the 2010 Winter Olympics in Vancouver. Wikipedia

Arianna Fontana.label: Arianna Fontana
Arianna Fontana.description: Arianna Fontana is an Italian short track speed skater, who won bronze in the 3000m relay at the 2006 Winter Olympics in Turin. She placed 11th in the 500m and 6th in the 1000m. Arianna specializes in the 500m event. Wikipedia

Charles Hamelin.label: Charles Hamelin
Charles Hamelin.description: Charles Hamelin is a Canadian short track speed skater from Sainte-Julie, Quebec. Hamelin is a 4-time Olympic medalist having won 3 gold and 1 silver during the 2006, 2010 and 2014 Winter Olympics. Wikipedia

Guillaume Bastille.label: Guillaume Bastille
Guillaume Bastille.description:
Guillaume Bastille is a Canadian short track speed skater from Rivière-du-Loup, Quebec.
He competed at the 2010 Winter Olympics in Vancouver in the men's 1500 metre short track and the men's 5000 metre relay competitions. Wikipedia

Kalyna Roberge.label: Kalyna Roberge
Kalyna Roberge.description:
Kalyna Roberge is a Canadian short track speed skater.
Roberge has won a gold medal in the 3000m relay at the 2005 World Championships. She also placed third overall at the 2005 World Junior Championships including a gold medal in the 500m. Wikipedia

Katarzyna Bachleda-Curuś.label: Katarzyna Bachleda-Curuś
Katarzyna Bachleda-Curuś.description: Katarzyna Bachleda-Curuś née Wójcicka is a Polish speed skater, who was born in Sanok and resides in Zakopane. Wikipedia

Katarzyna Woźniak.label: Katarzyna Woźniak
Katarzyna Woźniak.description: Katarzyna Woźniak is a Polish speed skater. She is a silver and bronze medalist of the Olympic Games. Wikipedia

Laurine van Riessen.label: Laurine Van Riessen
Laurine van Riessen.description: Laurine van Riessen is a long track speed skater who competed for the Netherlands at the 2010 Winter Olympics at the 500, 1000 and 1500 metre races. She won the bronze medal in the 1000 m. Wikipedia

Lee Jung-Su.label: Lee Jung-Su
Lee Jung-Su.description:
Lee Jung-Su is a South Korean short track speed skater. He is a two-time Olympic Champion from 2010 Winter Olympics.
Lee won one distances and became second overall at the 2008 World Junior Championships in Bolzano. Wikipedia
